            "endOffset": 140951,
            "parents": [],
            "secId": "se0010",
            "sentence": "Our main point in this note is to demonstrate that by applying a different reduction to a system one can handle lower order terms in the energy estimates.",
            "startOffset": 140797,
            "title": "Introduction"
        },
        {
            "endOffset": 141088,
            "parents": [],
            "secId": "se0010",
            "sentence": "For specific equations (e.g. second order equations) this result can be improved by other methods, but this lies outside our scope here.",
            "startOffset": 140952,
            "title": "Introduction"
        },
        {
            "endOffset": 148999,
            "parents": [],
            "secId": "se0030",
            "sentence": "One of the features of this result is that we can allow lower order terms to be complex-valued.",
            "startOffset": 148904,
            "title": "Results"
        },
        {
